Topics Covered
    Git vs GitHub
* Git is a version control system used to track changes in code
* GitHub is a platform used to store and manage Git repositories online
* Git works locally, while GitHub enables collaboration and remote access

    Repository Platforms
* GitLab – Provides repository hosting with built-in CI/CD features
* Bitbucket – Integrates well with Atlassian tools and supports Git repositories
* Azure Repos – Microsoft’s service for version control and project management
* AWS CodeCommit – Cloud-based repository service by AWS

